See the people the president met with
See the U.S. hot spots
President Trump’s physician has given an upbeat picture of his health. Medical experts warn that the president is entering a pivotal, unpredictable phase.
The outbreak at the White House underscores how difficult it is for a city with little control over the federal government it houses to sustain progress.
The president had immediate access to first-class treatment as well as doctors who have honed their understanding of the disease over several months.
Dr. Rick Bright, who said he was demoted for calling out a politicized coronavirus response, remains concerned about White House interference.
They echo misinformation that the president has spread for much of the year, as he has sought to minimize the threat of the virus.
Jerome Powell, the Federal Reserve chair, said the economy had “a long way to go” and urged stronger stimulus measures to avoid “unnecessary hardship.”
The guidelines make it highly unlikely that a coronavirus vaccine will be given emergency authorization by Election Day.
Former Attorney General Jeff Sessions enforced a “zero tolerance” policy on immigration that separated children from their parents. Doug Mills/The New York Times
House Lawmakers Condemn Big Tech’s ‘Monopoly Power’In a report led by Democrats, lawmakers said Apple, Amazon, Google and Facebook needed to be checked and recommended reforming antitrust laws.
Here are 12 accusations in the scathing report on the four tech giants.

From Gettysburg, Biden Calls for Healing of a ‘House Divided’“We have too bright a future to have it shipwrecked on the shoals of anger and hate and division,” Joe Biden said in a speech near the Civil War battlefield.
Kamala Harris and the Push to Cut Hospital Bills in CaliforniaShe took on the drug and hospital industry as California attorney general, seeking consumer relief from anti-competitive pricing.
Eddie Van Halen brought a joyous virtuosity to the electric guitar and was widely revered by his peers. John Munson/NJ Advance Media, via Associated Press
